		   <br /><span class="nobr"><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good  </span><br />
<br/><a href="/faction.html?faction=181;page=1;howmany=50#102387271721855"><img alt="" title="Use this to create a link to this post" src="/shared/garrowrt.png" border="0" height="9" width="11" /> Link to this post</a>
<br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1" alt=""/></span></td>
<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>Had a mage. Decided he wanted sow boots. Wanted to see if they'd work out of inventory slot since some class/race specific things will even if you're not of appropriate class/race. Okay. <br /> <br />ported mage and a druid to WC, ran both to north freeport. Bound near Bondl. loaded up circle of butcher. ported there and took an enchanter with. <br /> <br />pulled pegleg to ring. killed him. charmed spirit, now indiff to all. said last phrase. got gem. gated self and druid. chanter stays to keep spirit charmed. <br /> <br />went up to bondl. popped trade window with gem. invised from druid. clicked trade. faction. followed bondl to the point where he stops and asks his question - since he stands there for a bit. rebound there. ported back to butcher. got gem again. gate, repeat until desired faction. took him 10 or so times to go from dubious to amiable. <br /> <br />On an aside, he got the sow booties, 'your race/class/deity cannot use this item' some of you may say 'duh.' stranger things have worked. <br /> <br />Ah well, it was something to do. Xtik seemed to enjoy the fuzzy boots till mage reclaimed him. <br /></p>
</td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td class="fs8"></td></tr></table></td></tr></table>
