<div class="msgwrapper"><table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2"><a name="100600754726384"></a><span class="msgSubject">True Spirit Faction</span><br clear="all" />
		   <span class="sm">Posted: Nov 17th 2001 12:32pm<span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/faction.html?faction=181;mid=100600754726384#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a> </span></span></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" class="mform2" ><span class="fs8"><span class="notbold">By: </span><a href="/db/poster.html?user=119520"><span class="">Molnik</span></a><b><span class=""></span></b>
		   <br /><span class="nobr"><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good  </span><br />
<br/><a href="/faction.html?faction=181;page=1;howmany=50#100600754726384"><img alt="" title="Use this to create a link to this post" src="/shared/garrowrt.png" border="0" height="9" width="11" /> Link to this post</a>
<br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1" alt=""/></span></td>
<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>I was planning on advancing my epic when I got stopped at Camin in Erudin with an apprehensive faction. Went to all website and all I found to raise my faction with True Spirit was a post about the shaman quest with lesser spirit on Gormit Island. Verant, however, in their infinite wisdom had changed some things since the quest was last done and it was not functioning with camping to get a 15 seconds indifferent faction with all mobs when you relog.  Being apprehensive to the lesser spirit, I couldnt hail him to obtain the gem I needed to raise faction. I decided to go around the obstacle with this old trick.  <br />Most information you will find bellow were already posted. The person who posted it remained anon for some reason. To whomever that may be, thank you for the basics of the quest. I just edited his post to match what I did to raise my faction from apprehensive to indifferent.  <br /> <br />1.	Ask a high lvl Enchanter friend of yours if he can help for an hour or two. <br /> <br />2.	Take boat to OOT, go to Gornit Island and bind yourselves at loc. p680 n5325. <br /> <br />3.	 Set up the following hot keys. I numbered mine 1-4 just to make things easier.  <br />1. /say yes  <br />2. /say he threatened my life  <br />3. /say who are you  <br />4. /say I wish to know more  <br /> <br />4.	Kill Capt Surestout. He is in the tent. Lesser spirit spawns.  <br /> <br />5.	Enchanter now charms the lesser spirit. That will make him indifferent to you. <br /> <br />6.	Hail him. Hit your hot keys in order. No need to rush he is charmed. He should give you a tiny gem. <br /> <br />7.	Port you and your Enchanter friend to N Ro. run to N Freeport to the NW corner of the zone. (Near the building where they sell muffins) Jump in water swim through tunnel a short distance you will see a break in the wall with an NPC named Bondl Felligan. His loc is P460, N20. <br /> <br />8.	Now follow the order precisely here: 1- Hand Bondl the Gem. DO NOT HIT GIVE BUTTON RIGHT AWAY! If you are apprehensive you will lose gem.  2- Ask your enchanter to cast invis on you. Once invis, you become indifferent to him.  3-Now is time to press GIVE button. <br /> <br />9.	Your faction with True Spirit got better. <br />You gain party experience.  <br /> <br />10.	Gate to bind point, repeat. Lesser may still be up for a couple of trips. Check faction till you are indifferent to Bondl(Remember the spirit is charmed and will con indifferent to you.). <br /> <br />Final notes. I had to do this quest 6 times to get from apprehensive to indiff. Binding there helps a lot because of downtime that would be caused by the boat ride. Once you are indifferent you no longer need the help of the enchanter to charm the spirit and invis you in NFP. The Enchanter helping me did the quest along with me. Why not? He is there and has to go both location of quest. Good faction with someone cannot hurt you can it?J Thank you Elvorfing (Enchanter extraordinaire) for helping with this quest. <br /> <br />Good Luck to you all  <br /> <br />Molnik Hanneken, Wizard of Tholuxe Pealls <br /> <br /> <br /></p>
<br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Molnik Hanneken, Wizard</td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td class="fs8"></td><td align="right" class="fs8" >1 reply</td></tr></table></td></tr></table>
